MRP Rocky Road Initial Reactive Rate Schedule

record_data.record_plain_text:
MRP ROCKY ROAD LLC
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE MRP Rocky Road LLC ("Seller") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from Seller’s generation facility located in East Dundee, Illinois and interconnected to the Commonwealth Edison Company ("ComEd") transmission system, which is under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Rate Schedule sets forth Seller’s revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from Seller’s generation facility to PJM and ComEd. Seller’s fixed revenue requirement consists of the Fixed Capability Component. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. REVENUE REQUIREMENT Total Annual Revenue Requirement is $285,000 Total Monthly Revenue Requirement is $285,000/12 = $23,750
